AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp;Biografilm Festival unveils a new title planned for its twentieth edition, from June 7 to 17 in Bologna. This is 'Before the end. The last days of Enrico Berlinguer' by Samuele Rossi, the result of a long research work aimed at telling a crucial and exciting moment in the history of our country.<br> It was on June 7, 1984 when Enrico Berlinguer, during a constituency in Padua >, warns an obvious malore: Despite everything, in those moments, he brings to the bottom his speech addressed to the crowd, but shortly there he enters the coma: He'll die after four days on June 11th. On 13 June the most impressive political funeral of the history of the Republic takes place in Rome: in two million go down the square for his funeral, something never seen before. An event that indelibly marked the history of Italy.
&nbsp;
'Before the end. The last days of Enrico Berlinguer' wants to return the collective memory of that event through an exciting storytelling > and innovative built with the only use of archive material from national and international archives. The film proposes an accurate and renewed narrative and visual reconstruction of those 7 days that upset Italy. It tells with a new perspective a moment of passage and an end: that of a beloved politician, of a whole party, of a country idea, perhaps even the end of an era. The film is produced by the Echivisivi by Samuele Rossi and Giuseppe Cassaro with Salice Production by Cosetta Lagani and Solaria Film by Emanuele Nespeca.
&nbsp;
In the common intent to remember one of the protagonists of the history of the twentieth century, the film event of Biografilm linked to the world premiere screening of Prima della fine. The last days of Enrico Berlinguer dialogues with the multimedia exhibition> 'The places and words of Enrico Berlinguer' that will be inaugurated on June 11 in Bologna at the Archaeological Civic Museum, exactly forty years after the death of the leader of the Pci. The exhibition reconstructs the political and personal path through original video, photo and autograph documents. Also presented are the political posters elaborated in the years of the Berlinguer secretariat, as well as photographs of author, books, insights. &nbsp;

